p <!-- -->sesame oil</li><li class="pb-xxs pt-xxs list-item list-item--separator">160g <!-- -->green beans</li><li class="pb-xxs pt-xxs list-item list-item--separator">200g <!-- -->straight-to-wok noodles</li><li class="pb-xxs pt-xxs list-item list-item--separator"><a class="link link--styled" href="/glossary/soy-sauce-glossary">soy sauce</a></li><li class="pb-xxs pt-xxs list-item list-item--separator">fresh coriander leaves</li><li class="pb-xxs pt-xxs list-item list-item--separator">sesame seeds</li></ul></section></section><section class="recipe__method-steps mb-lg col-12 col-lg-6"><h3 class="mb-xs section-heading-1">Method</h3><div class="grouped-list"><ul class="grouped-list__list list"><li class="pb-xs pt-xs list-item"><span class="mb-xxs heading-6">STEP 1</span><div class="editor-content"><p>Squeeze the sausages out of their skins. Mix the sausagemeat with thegarlic, ginger and red chilli, then fry in the sesame oil until browned. Add the green beans, then fry for 1 min more.</p></div></li><li class="pb-xs pt-xs list-item"><span class="mb-xxs heading-6">STEP 2</span><div class="editor-content"><p>Tip in the straight-to-wok noodles and a splash ofsoy sauce, and toss together. Add a splash of water and put the lid on to allow the beans to steam for a couple of mins. Sprinkle with fresh coriander leaves and sesame seeds to serve.</p></div></li></ul></div></section></div><div class="post__content-end row hidden-print"><div class="col-12"><section class="mb-xl"><h3 class="case-uppercase mb-xs heading-5">Goes well with</h3><div class="editor-content"></div></section></div></div><p class="post__publication-link hidden-print">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <!-- -->April 2018</p></div><div></div><div><div class="OUTBRAIN hidden-print" data-src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/spicy-sausage-noodles" data-widget-id="AR_5"></div></div><ul class="pocket hidden-print mb-lg list"><li class="list-item"><div class="pb-lg" id="commentsFeed"><h2 class="pt-md pb-md heading-